1.00	1951%E2%80%9352_Chicago_Black_Hawks_season	1951–52 Chicago Black Hawks season	The 1951–52 Chicago Black Hawks season was the team's twenty-sixth season in the NHL, and they were coming off of a horrible season in 1950–51, when they finished with an NHL worst record of 13–47–10, earning 36 points, as Chicago missed the playoffs for the fifth straight season. The Black Hawks ended the 1950–51 season winning only two of their last 43 games.	
